==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Dolly Varden
<hw>Dol"ly Var"den</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <sn>1.</sn> <def>A character in
Dickens's novel ⟦ldquo⟧Barnaby Rudge,⟦rdquo⟧ a beautiful, lively, and
coquettish girl who wore a cherry-colored mantle and cherry-colored
ribbons.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A style of light, bright-figured dress goods for
women; also, a style of dress.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Dolly Varden trout</b></col> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>a
trout of northwest America; -- called also <altname>bull
trout</altname>, <altname>malma</altname>, and <altname>red-spotted
trout</altname>. See <er>Malma</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>dolma</ent>⟦br⟧
